@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxAccordion))]
@attribute [Route("/components/" + nameof(HxAccordionItem))]

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxAccordion)">
	<DocAlert Type="DocAlertType.Warning">
		Avoid using a constant value for <code>@nameof(HxAccordion.ExpandedItemId)</code>,
		as it resets the accordion to that specific item on each roundtrip.
		Instead, utilize <code>@nameof(HxAccordion.InitialExpandedItemId)</code>
		for setting the initial state.
	</DocAlert>

	<DocHeading Title="Basic usage" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxAccordion_PlainDemo)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Flush" />
	<p>
		Apply the <code>.accordion-flush</code> class to eliminate
		the default <code>background-color</code>, certain borders, and rounded corners,
		allowing accordions to extend edge-to-edge alongside their parent container.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxAccordion_Demo_Flush)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Stay open" />
	<p>
		By default, only one accordion item can be expanded at a time.
		To allow multiple items to be expanded at the same time,
		set the <code>StayOpen</code> parameter to <code>true</code>.
	</p>
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxAccordion_Demo_StayOpen)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Complex demo" />
	<Demo Type="typeof(HxAccordion_ComplexDemo)" />

	<DocHeading Title="Accessibility" />
	<p>
		<code>HxAccordion</code> is built on the native <code>&lt;details&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;summary&gt;</code> elements,
		so the browser provides the disclosure semantics and keyboard support (<kbd>Enter</kbd>/<kbd>Space</kbd> toggles a section) out of the box.
		When only one item may be open at a time (the default), the items share an HTML <code>name</code> attribute so the browser enforces the single-open behavior natively.
	</p>
</ApiDoc>

<ApiDoc Type="typeof(HxAccordionItem)" />